			    STPJS 328</div>
  <p class="std">The first principles of the Gospel,<span class="footRef">1</span> as I believe, are, faith, repentance, baptism for the remission
  of sins,<span class="footRef">2</span> with the promise of the Holy Ghost.<span class="footRef">3</span></p>
  <p class="std">Look at Heb. 6:1 contradictions&mdash;&ldquo;Therefore leaving the principles of the doctrine of Christ,
  let us go on unto perfection.&rdquo;<span class="footRef">4</span> If a man leaves the principles of the doctrine of Christ, how can he
  be saved in the principles? This is contradiction. I don&rsquo;t believe it. I will render it as it should
  be&mdash;&ldquo;Therefore not leaving the principles of the doctrine of Christ, let us go on unto perfection, not
  laying again the foundation of repentance from dead works, and of faith toward God, of the doctrine
  of baptisms, and of laying on of hands, and of resurrection of the dead, and of eternal judgment.&rdquo;<span class="footRef">5</span></p>
  <div class="topic">The Kingdom of God</div>
  <p class="std">It is one thing to see the kingdom of God, and another thing to enter into it.<span class="footRef">6</span> We must have a
  change of heart<span class="footRef">7</span> to see the kingdom of God, and subscribe the articles of adoption to enter therein.</p>
  <p class="std">No man can receive the Holy Ghost without receiving revelations.<span class="footRef">8</span> The Holy Ghost is a
  revelator.<span class="footRef">9</span></p>
  <div class="topic">Punishments Await this Generation</div>
  <p class="std">I prophesy, in the name of the Lord God<span class="footRef">10</span> of Israel, anguish and wrath<span class="footRef">11</span> and tribulation and the
  withdrawing of the Spirit of God from the earth<span class="footRef">12</span> await this generation, until they are visited with
  utter desolation.<span class="footRef">13</span> This generation is as corrupt<span class="footRef">14</span> as the generation of the Jews that crucified Christ;<span class="footRef">15</span>
  and if He were here to-day, and should preach the same doctrine He did then, they would put Him
  to death. I defy all the world to destroy the work of God;<span class="footRef">16</span> and I prophesy they never will have
  power to kill me till my work is accomplished,<span class="footRef">17</span> and I am ready to die.<span class="footRef">18</span></p>
  <p class="wideEllipse">* * *</p>

  <div class="topic">Temporal Economy&mdash;Care of the Poor</div>
  <p class="std">The temporal economy of this people should be to establish and encourage manufactures, and
  not to take usury<span class="footRef">19</span> for their money. I do not want to bind the poor here to starve.<span class="footRef">20</span> Go out into the
  country and into the neighboring cities, and get food, and gird up your loins, and be sober.<span class="footRef">21</span> When
  you get food, return, if you have a mind to.</p>
